WEBVTT

00:02.883 --> 00:04.715
Meredith:
THERE'S THIS THING I USED TO DO

00:04.715 --> 00:07.468
WHEN I WAS A KID
TO MY MOM'S VCR.

00:07.468 --> 00:11.302
I'D TAKE IT APART
PIECE BY PIECE,

00:11.302 --> 00:13.264
THEN PUT IT BACK TOGETHER
AGAIN.

00:13.264 --> 00:15.346
I LEFT MY PHONE
AT THE LAB.

00:15.346 --> 00:17.098
BY THE TIME I FIGURED OUT
I LEFT IT,

00:17.098 --> 00:19.230
I WAS ALREADY AT THE AIRPORT
COMING TO YOU.

00:19.230 --> 00:21.021
AND SHE PICKED UP YOUR PHONE
WHY?
I DON'T KNOW.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.524
SHE PROBABLY THOUGHT IT WAS ME.
I CALLED HER FROM THE AIRPORT.

00:23.524 --> 00:25.526
THEN SHE TOLD ME
SHE SPOKE TO YOU.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.198
BUT INEVITABLY,

00:27.198 --> 00:29.950
THERE WAS ALWAYS
A PIECE OR TWO LEFT OVER,

00:29.950 --> 00:32.032
SOMETHING I DIDN'T QUITE KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH.

00:32.032 --> 00:34.075
IS THAT IS? IS THAT EVERYTHING
YOU HAVE TO SAY?

00:34.075 --> 00:35.536
THAT'S ALL THERE IS TO SAY.

00:35.536 --> 00:38.038
I'VE TOLD YOU EVERYTHING,
THE WHOLE STORY -- ALL OF IT.

00:38.038 --> 00:40.081
BUT IF YOU WANT,
I'LL GO THROUGH IT ALL AGAIN.

00:40.081 --> 00:42.002
AND SHE'S
YOUR RESEARCH FELLOW.
YES.

00:42.002 --> 00:44.085
JUST YOUR RESEARCH FELLOW.

00:44.085 --> 00:46.427
SO, WHAT DO YOU DO
WITH THAT PIECE?

00:46.427 --> 00:47.468
MEREDITH.

00:47.468 --> 00:48.799
I WISH
I COULD BELIEVE YOU.

00:48.799 --> 00:49.930
YOU CAN. I'M HERE.

00:49.930 --> 00:51.342
I KNOW HOW THIS WORKS.

00:51.342 --> 00:53.134
I WAS YOUR RESIDENT ONCE.

00:53.134 --> 00:54.305
IT SEEMS LIKE
YOU CAME HOME

00:54.305 --> 00:56.227
BECAUSE YOU THOUGHT
YOU WERE IN TROUBLE.

00:56.227 --> 00:57.348
DO YOU TRY
TO FIT IT BACK IN?

00:57.348 --> 00:59.600
I CAME HOME
BECAUSE WE'RE IN TROUBLE.

00:59.600 --> 01:02.353
I CAME HOME TO WORK ON THIS,
ON US.

01:02.353 --> 01:04.064
I CAME HOME.

01:04.064 --> 01:06.317
DO YOU TRY TO MAKE IT WORK?

01:08.689 --> 01:11.402
I HAVE TO
GET TO THE HOSPITAL.

01:11.402 --> 01:14.074
CAN'T YOU GET SOMEBODY
TO COVER?

01:14.074 --> 01:17.658
OR DO YOU DECIDE YOU CAN LIVE
WITHOUT THAT MISSING PIECE?

01:17.658 --> 01:19.910
[ SIGHS ]

01:19.910 --> 01:21.872
YOU SHOULD SPEND THE DAY
WITH THE KIDS. THEY'D LOVE IT.

01:21.872 --> 01:23.124
THEY REALLY MISS YOU.

01:23.124 --> 01:25.206
[ DOOR OPENS ]

01:31.262 --> 01:32.973
Derek: WHO IS NEXT?

01:32.973 --> 01:35.306
UH, WE'RE LOOKING AT
NEUROPEPTIDE "Y" RECEPTORS

01:35.306 --> 01:36.517
IN MARMOSET BRAINS.

01:36.517 --> 01:38.519
GREAT.
THAT'S -- THAT'S GREAT.

01:38.519 --> 01:39.810
WHICH ONE OF YOU
IS DOING A THING

01:39.810 --> 01:41.142
WHERE YOU'RE PATCH-CLAMPING
NERVE CELLS?

01:41.142 --> 01:42.273
OH, THAT'S ME.

01:43.023 --> 01:45.186
WHICH ONE OF YOU IS "ME"?
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

01:45.186 --> 01:47.528
UH, COLLIER.
RENEE COLLIER.

01:47.528 --> 01:50.281
RENEE, HOW'S IT GOING?

01:50.281 --> 01:52.153
PRETTY GOOD.
HOW ARE YOU?

01:52.153 --> 01:54.155
I MEAN WITH THE RESEARCH, RENEE.
HOW'S IT GOING?

01:54.155 --> 01:56.907
[ GROUP CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
OH. [ CHUCKLES ] UH, IT'S --
IT'S GOING PRETTY WELL.

01:56.907 --> 01:58.949
A FEW BUMPS IN THE ROAD,
BUT ALL THINGS CONSIDERED...

01:58.949 --> 02:01.041
THE SYNAPTIC TIMING DISCOVERIES
YOU MADE

02:01.041 --> 02:02.793
WILL HELP US HERE
IMMENSELY.

02:02.793 --> 02:05.005
I WANT TO SEE
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

02:05.005 --> 02:07.298
OH, SURE.

02:07.298 --> 02:10.171
I LOOK FORWARD
TO WORKING WITH YOU.

02:26.647 --> 02:27.648
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

02:27.648 --> 02:28.859
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

02:28.859 --> 02:30.481
17-YEAR-OLD WITH HISTORY
OF BILIARY ATRESIA.

02:30.481 --> 02:32.233
CHRONIC LIVER REJECTION.

02:32.233 --> 02:35.115
UH, WAITING ON DONORS,
BUT HE KEEPS DETERIORATING.

02:35.115 --> 02:36.987
I'M --
I'M RUNNING OUT OF IDEAS.

02:36.987 --> 02:38.239
LET ME TAKE A LOOK.

02:38.239 --> 02:40.241
I DIDN'T PULL YOU OUT OF ZOLA'S
DANCE CLASS OR SOMETHING, DID I?

02:40.241 --> 02:41.992
NO, NO.
DEREK'S HOME, THOUGH.

02:41.992 --> 02:43.704
SINCE WHEN?
LAST NIGHT.

02:43.704 --> 02:45.496
AND THIS MORNING.
AND?

02:45.496 --> 02:48.249
AND WHAT?
AND DO YOU KNOW WHO
ANSWERED HIS PHONE?

02:48.249 --> 02:50.341
HIS BILIARY OUTFLOW
IS STRICTURED.

02:50.341 --> 02:53.384
I WANT TO EXAMINE HIM MYSELF
AND GET A NEW ULTRASOUND.

02:56.096 --> 02:58.178
OWEN!

02:58.178 --> 02:59.260
UH, CHIEF.

02:59.260 --> 03:01.181
HEY, DR. SHEPHERD.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.143
YOU FINISHED YOUR LAMINECTOMY
IN O.R. TWO?

03:03.143 --> 03:04.975
I DID.
UH, DID YOU NEED...?

03:04.975 --> 03:08.359
OH, I'M JUST TRYING TO SEE
IF BAILEY CAN GET IN HERE

03:08.359 --> 03:10.150
FOR A BOWEL OBSTRUCTION.

03:10.150 --> 03:12.022
RIGHT.

03:12.022 --> 03:14.194
O.R.'s ALL HERS.
GREAT.

03:14.194 --> 03:18.028
I FELT LIKE LAST NIGHT'S
BUSINESS WAS LEFT...UNFINISHED.

03:18.028 --> 03:19.240
YOU FELT THAT WAY, TOO?

03:19.240 --> 03:21.742
MANY AGENDA ITEMS
LEFT UNCHECKED.

03:21.742 --> 03:23.994
YEAH, BARELY SCRATCHED
THE SURFACE, REALLY.

03:23.994 --> 03:25.035
I THINK
WE NEED A FOLLOW-UP.

03:25.035 --> 03:26.497
AGREED.

03:26.497 --> 03:29.330
WHEN WE WON'T
BE...INTERRUPTED.

03:29.330 --> 03:30.791
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:30.791 --> 03:32.883
[ CELLPHONE MOOS ]
OH, MY GOD.

03:32.883 --> 03:35.095
[ CHUCKLES ]
HEY, HOW ABOUT --

03:35.095 --> 03:38.178
HOW ABOUT TONIGHT,
IF YOU'RE NOT ON CALL?

03:38.178 --> 03:40.140
I'M NOT.

03:40.140 --> 03:41.682
O-OKAY, THEN.

03:41.682 --> 03:43.474
OKAY.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.691
[ SIGHS ]

03:50.691 --> 03:52.813
HEY, JO,
I NEED YOUR HELP.

03:52.813 --> 03:54.815
NO, I'M NOT LETTING YOU DO
LAUNDRY AT THE HOUSE AGAIN.

03:54.815 --> 03:56.817
ALEX GETS CRABBY WHEN YOU
LEAVE YOUR SOGGY CLOTHES

03:56.817 --> 03:58.068
IN THE WASHER.
STOP.

03:58.068 --> 04:00.200
I SPENT SO MUCH TIME WITH
DR. SHEPHERD ON THAT BRAIN TUMOR

04:00.200 --> 04:02.453
THAT I'M BEHIND IN LIKE
EVERY OTHER SPECIALTY.

04:02.453 --> 04:04.365
I JUST CHECKED MY HOURS.
I AM SO SCREWED.

04:04.365 --> 04:05.706
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:05.706 --> 04:07.628
[ Posh accent ] SUDDENLY
IT'S LONELY ON THE NEURO THRONE.

04:07.628 --> 04:09.079
HEY, WILSON, EDWARDS.

04:09.079 --> 04:10.791
I'VE GOT A LACERATED SPLEEN
IN 20 MINUTES,

04:10.791 --> 04:12.423
AND HUNT HAD A PERSONAL MATTER
COME UP.

04:12.423 --> 04:13.924
I NEED SOMEONE DOWNSTAIRS.

04:13.924 --> 04:15.836
START WITH THE HEADACHE
IN BED 3.

04:15.836 --> 04:17.638
WILSON, IT'S YOURS.

04:17.638 --> 04:18.969
WHAT DID I JUST SAY?

04:18.969 --> 04:20.220
[ Normal voice ]
SHE SAID "HEADACHE."

04:20.220 --> 04:21.972
IT'S PROBABLY NEURO.
I'M DOING YOU A FAVOR.

04:21.972 --> 04:23.844
FINE. BUT IF IT'S SOMETHING
GOOD, YOU BETTER CALL ME.

04:23.844 --> 04:24.975
FINE.

04:24.975 --> 04:27.057
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
I JUST GOT A PAGE?

04:27.057 --> 04:29.019
OH. YEAH. NOW,
I DON'T WANT YOU TO WORRY.

04:29.019 --> 04:30.851
SHE'S UNDERSTANDABLY
EMBARRASSED,

04:30.851 --> 04:32.893
SO WE WENT AHEAD
AND PUT HER IN TRAUMA ONE.

04:32.893 --> 04:35.065
RICHARD, WHAT ARE YOU --
OKAY, NOW,
SHE'S SHAKEN UP, OKAY?

04:35.065 --> 04:37.157
SHE'S GOT A BIG BRUISE
ON HER BACK,

04:37.157 --> 04:39.279
AND -- AND ASIDE FROM
A NASTY HEAD LAC,

04:39.279 --> 04:40.991
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE
OF OTHER INJURIES.

04:40.991 --> 04:43.033
SHEPHERD'S WITH HER NOW.
WHO ARE WE TALKING ABOUT?

04:43.033 --> 04:44.995
I THOUGHT THEY TOLD YOU.

04:47.037 --> 04:48.459
MOM!
WHAT HAPPENED?!

04:48.459 --> 04:50.411
FOR HEAVEN'S SAKE, OWEN,
SHUT THAT CURTAIN.

04:50.411 --> 04:52.082
EVERYONE CAN SEE ME.

04:52.082 --> 04:53.754
EVELYN,
TRY NOT TO MOVE, OKAY?

04:53.754 --> 04:55.626
ALREADY GAVE HALF
THE NEIGHBORHOOD A FREE SHOW

04:55.626 --> 04:57.177
JUST BY GETTING
IN THE AMBULANCE.

04:57.177 --> 04:59.089
SHE FELL IN THE SHOWER,
RIGHT THROUGH THE GLASS DOOR.

04:59.089 --> 05:01.472
DID YOU SLIP? I TOLD YOU
YOU NEED A SUPPORT BAR IN THERE.

05:01.472 --> 05:03.093
OH,
THOSE THINGS ARE SO UGLY.

05:03.093 --> 05:05.095
SHE SAID SHE GOT DIZZY.
DIZZINESS, HUH?

05:05.095 --> 05:07.137
I'M NOT SURPRISED
WITH A LACERATION LIKE THIS.

05:07.137 --> 05:08.479
YOU HAD QUITE A FALL.

05:08.479 --> 05:10.641
I-I THINK
WE SHOULD GET A HEAD C.T.

05:10.641 --> 05:12.483
SHE SAID SHE WAS DIZZY
BEFORE THE FALL.

05:12.483 --> 05:14.645
ALL MORNING, ACTUALLY.
REALLY?

05:14.645 --> 05:16.937
WE GOT THIS FROM HERE.
THANK YOU. YOU CAN STEP OUTSIDE.

05:16.937 --> 05:19.940
NO, I WANT HIM TO SAY. JOHN
WAS WITH ME WHEN IT HAPPENED.

05:19.940 --> 05:21.782
I KNOW, MOM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:21.782 --> 05:24.204
YOU'VE BEEN GREAT, THANK YOU.
MY MOM'S REALLY GRATEFUL.

05:24.204 --> 05:26.407
BUT HE'S DONE HIS PART NOW, MOM,
SO...

05:26.407 --> 05:29.580
NO,
I DON'T MEAN SINCE I FELL.

05:29.580 --> 05:32.953
HE WAS WITH ME
WHEN I FELL.

05:34.545 --> 05:38.048
[ CHUCKLES ]
I-I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

05:38.048 --> 05:40.631
WELL, I WASN'T WITH HER
IN THE SHOWER.

05:40.631 --> 05:43.173
I WAS, UH -- I WAS MAKING
US SOME BREAKFAST
BEFORE I WENT TO WORK.

05:47.848 --> 05:50.230
OWEN, I'M JOHN.

05:51.732 --> 05:54.775
AS IN..."JOHN."

05:54.775 --> 05:57.147
YEAH, I-I STILL
DON'T UNDERSTAND.

05:57.147 --> 05:59.440
HONEY,
JOHN AND I, WE'RE --

05:59.440 --> 06:02.443
I THOUGHT YOU TOLD HIM.

06:02.443 --> 06:04.825
TOLD ME WHAT?

06:06.156 --> 06:08.078
IS SOMEBODY GONNA TELL ME
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

06:08.078 --> 06:10.200
I THINK
WHAT THEY'RE TRYING TO SAY

06:10.200 --> 06:14.585
IS JOHN IS...
YOUR MOTHER'S BOYFRIEND.

06:14.585 --> 06:16.126
[ STAMMERS ]

06:27.217 --> 06:28.388
HOW LONG HAS THIS BEEN GOING ON?

06:28.388 --> 06:29.600
SHE WAS DIZZY
WHEN SHE FIRST GOT OUT OF BED.

06:29.600 --> 06:31.391
WE THOUGHT SHE WAS JUST HUNGRY,
SO I-I --

06:31.391 --> 06:33.393
THAT'S NOT WHAT I --
[ SIGHS ]

06:33.393 --> 06:34.515
HOW LONG HAVE YOU TWO BEEN...

06:34.515 --> 06:35.856
IN A RELATIONSHIP?

06:35.856 --> 06:37.978
MOM, PLEASE.
PLEASE DON'T USE THAT WORD.

06:37.978 --> 06:39.359
EVELYN,
ANY CHANGES IN VISION?

06:39.359 --> 06:40.731
NO, DEAR.

06:40.731 --> 06:42.823
WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER
A LITTLE UNDER A YEAR.
A YEAR?!

06:42.823 --> 06:44.194
DR. WEBBER,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

06:44.194 --> 06:45.946
MORE X-RAYS, MAYBE,
ON HER LEFT WRIST?

06:45.946 --> 06:47.988
UH, I-I DIDN'T REALIZE
SHE HAD HURT --

06:47.988 --> 06:49.329
JUST TO BE SAFE.

06:49.329 --> 06:51.161
SURE, SURE.

06:51.161 --> 06:52.292
THAT'S A FINE IDEA,
SHEPHERD.

06:52.292 --> 06:54.164
OWEN, JOHN'S VERY NICE.

06:54.164 --> 06:55.956
I THINK YOU TWO
HAVE A LOT IN COMMON.

06:55.956 --> 06:57.297
SHE TALKS ABOUT YOU
ALL THE TIME. SHE'S SO PROUD.

06:57.297 --> 06:58.629
I'M THRILLED
THAT WE'RE FINALLY MEETING.

06:58.629 --> 07:00.170
HOW OLD ARE YOU?!

07:00.170 --> 07:01.211
DON'T BE RUDE.
35.

07:01.211 --> 07:02.883
HE'S YOUNG ENOUGH
TO BE MY BROTHER.

07:02.883 --> 07:04.925
DOES HE HAVE ACCESS
TO YOUR FINANCIAL INFORMATION,

07:04.925 --> 07:06.096
YOUR PENSION FUND?
OWEN HUNT!

07:06.096 --> 07:08.809
OKAY, PUPILS ARE EQUAL
AND REACTIVE.

07:08.809 --> 07:10.220
THIS IS A SERIOUS
RELATIONSHIP.

07:10.220 --> 07:12.052
BUT I'D STILL LIKE TO GET
THAT HEAD C.T.

07:12.052 --> 07:13.894
JUST TO RULE OUT
A BLEED.
Owen: "SERIOUS." SURE, OKAY.

07:13.894 --> 07:16.647
SERIOUSLY WEIRD,
SERIOUSLY MISGUIDED.

07:16.647 --> 07:18.058
NOT THAT
WE DON'T HAVE OUR FUN.

07:18.058 --> 07:19.560
HEY, HEY, HEY, STAY AWAY
FROM HER! YOU HEAR ME?!

07:19.560 --> 07:22.192
WHOA, BUDDY, CALM DOWN.
I'M NOT YOUR BUDDY, OKAY?

07:22.192 --> 07:23.654
I'LL BE CHANGING
HER PASSWORDS,

07:23.654 --> 07:24.985
HER LOCKS,
HER PHONE NUMBER.

07:24.985 --> 07:26.366
IF YOU SO MUCH AS ATTEMPT --

07:26.366 --> 07:28.068
Richard: HUNT!

07:28.068 --> 07:29.990
LET'S TAKE A WALK.

07:32.703 --> 07:33.834
TAKE A WALK.

07:47.087 --> 07:49.349
HEY, DANNY.
WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

07:49.349 --> 07:52.222
PROBABLY TRYING TO FIND
MORE STUPID STUFF

07:52.222 --> 07:53.473
TO CRAM IN THIS ROOM.

07:53.473 --> 07:54.805
DR. GREY, MEET DANNY,

07:54.805 --> 07:56.937
GREY-SLOAN'S
RESIDENT HOCKEY FREAK.

07:56.937 --> 07:59.600
NICE TO MEET YOU, DANNY.
DO YOU MIND IF I, UH...

07:59.600 --> 08:01.902
HEY, DID YOU SEE THE GAME
LAST NIGHT?

08:01.902 --> 08:03.483
YEAH,
YOU OWE ME 10 BUCKS.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.235
SHARP HAD FIVE SHOTS
ON GOAL.

08:05.235 --> 08:06.607
YEAH,
AND NONE WENT IN.

08:06.607 --> 08:08.569
DR. KAREV, ANY NEWS?

08:08.569 --> 08:10.911
WE'LL, UH,
AFTER TODAY'S SCARE,

08:10.911 --> 08:12.573
WE RAN ANOTHER SET
OF BLOOD TESTS.

08:12.573 --> 08:14.745
WE THINK HE'S DEVELOPING
ANOTHER INFECTION.

08:14.745 --> 08:16.456
WELL, CAN WE DO
THE CATHETER PROCEDURE AGAIN

08:16.456 --> 08:18.749
AND DRAIN THE INFECTION?
WELL, WE CAN TRY, BUT...

08:18.749 --> 08:22.042
ACTUALLY, AFTER LOOKING AT
DANNY'S SCANS AND ULTRASOUNDS,

08:22.042 --> 08:24.214
I THINK WE COULD GO IN
SURGICALLY.

08:24.214 --> 08:25.796
COULD RE-CREATE
THE BILIARY TREE

08:25.796 --> 08:27.678
AND PREVENT INFECTION
FROM REOCCURRING.

08:27.678 --> 08:30.050
IS THAT AN OPTION?
UH, IT'S A RISKY ONE
IN DANNY'S STATE.

08:30.050 --> 08:32.763
I-I'D PREFER TO CONTINUE
WITH ANTIBIOTIC THERAPY

08:32.763 --> 08:34.394
AND JUST KEEP
MONITORING HIM.

08:34.394 --> 08:35.976
BUT THE SURGERY
COULD HELP DANNY

08:35.976 --> 08:37.397
WHILE HE'S WAITING
FOR A NEW LIVER

08:37.397 --> 08:39.770
AND POSSIBLY GET HIM OUT OF
THE HOSPITAL FOR A WHILE.

08:39.770 --> 08:41.902
WELL, I'M IN.
LIVING HERE SUCKS.

08:41.902 --> 08:43.273
WELL, LET'S NOT JUMP
INTO ANYTHING YET.

08:43.273 --> 08:45.856
DR. GREY AND I WILL DISCUSS IT
BEFORE WE SERIOUSLY CONSIDER --

08:45.856 --> 08:47.147
WELL, WHY DON'T WE
RUN SOME MORE TESTS,

08:47.147 --> 08:50.150
AND, UH, WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHAT WE THINK, OKAY?

08:51.321 --> 08:55.205
SO, YOU'VE HAD THIS HEADACHE
FOR A MONTH WITH NO RELIEF?

08:55.205 --> 08:56.917
HMM. OKAY.

08:56.917 --> 08:59.039
AND WHERE IS THE HEADACHE
LOCATED?

08:59.039 --> 09:01.662
ALL OVER.
IT -- IT MOVES AROUND.

09:01.662 --> 09:04.164
LISTEN, I WENT TO CHINA
LAST MONTH.

09:04.164 --> 09:05.836
IS THIS THE BIRD FLU?

09:05.836 --> 09:08.008
OR THE -- THE -- WHAT --
WHAT IS IT, THE SARS?

09:08.008 --> 09:10.510
IT'S ONE OF THOSE.
I HAVE A HEADACHE ALL THE TIME.

09:10.510 --> 09:12.432
I GET THESE NOSEBLEEDS.
NOSEBLEEDS?

09:12.432 --> 09:14.384
YEAH,
THE BLOOD STARTS TO COME OUT,

09:14.384 --> 09:16.096
AND THEN I GOT AT IT
WITH A TISSUE,

09:16.096 --> 09:17.177
AND IT JUST GOES BACK UP.

09:17.177 --> 09:19.059
HUH.

09:19.059 --> 09:20.060
IS THAT NORMAL?

09:21.642 --> 09:23.854
SEE, YOU'RE PUTTING ON A MASK.
I'VE GOT THE SARS.

09:23.854 --> 09:25.185
NO,
THIS IS JUST PROTOCOL.

09:26.777 --> 09:30.240
OH, HEY, I SEE WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

09:31.652 --> 09:33.573
OH, GOD.
GOD, WHAT?!

09:33.573 --> 09:35.245
THAT'S NOT A NOSEBLEED.

09:35.245 --> 09:37.157
[ WHIMPERS ]

09:37.157 --> 09:40.751
SO, DR. AVERY ATTACHED THE
TRANSPLANTED TISSUE TO THE ARM.

09:40.751 --> 09:43.624
AND, AS DESCRIBED IN THIS
MORNING'S PRESENTATION...

09:43.624 --> 09:47.047
THE FRESH BLOOD SUPPLY HAS
ALLOWED THE SKIN TO REGROW

09:47.047 --> 09:49.169
WITHOUT THE NEED
FOR FURTHER GRAFTS.

09:49.169 --> 09:50.260
DR. WARREN?

09:50.260 --> 09:52.172
DR. AVERY WILL PERFORM

09:52.172 --> 09:55.425
A PRIMARY MICROVASCULAR
ATERIAL REPAIR FIRST

09:55.425 --> 09:57.177
AND THEN FOLLOW
WITH A VENOUS ANASTOMOSIS.

09:57.177 --> 09:59.059
ALL RIGHT, MATT.
THIS ALL LOOKS VERY GOOD.

09:59.059 --> 10:00.851
WE'RE GONNA SEE YOU
IN THE O.R.
WHAT?

10:00.851 --> 10:01.852
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:01.852 --> 10:03.063
I SWEAR
THAT NEVER GETS OLD.

10:03.063 --> 10:04.895
AH, IF ONLY
THAT WERE TRUE.

10:04.895 --> 10:06.606
OKAY, GUYS.

10:06.606 --> 10:08.568
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

10:08.568 --> 10:10.901
EXCUSE ME.
ALL RIGHT.

10:12.993 --> 10:13.994
Stephanie: HEY.

10:13.994 --> 10:15.155
EDWARDS.

10:15.155 --> 10:17.117
YOU NEED ANYTHING?

10:17.117 --> 10:18.368
YOU ARE PRETTY.

10:18.368 --> 10:20.080
I'M SORRY?

10:20.080 --> 10:23.003
DO YOU NEED ANYTHING?
DO YOU WANT ANYTHING?

10:23.003 --> 10:25.625
OKAY, THAT'S, UH -- THAT'S --
THAT'S FLATTERING.

10:25.625 --> 10:29.840
BUT, UM, I HAVE A BEAUTIFUL
AND VERY STRONG WIFE.

10:29.840 --> 10:32.382
EW, WARREN.
NO, I WANT YOUR CASE.

10:32.382 --> 10:35.465
OH. [ LAUGHS ]
NO, NOT A CHANCE.

10:35.465 --> 10:37.097
I WILL GIVE YOU $50.

10:38.178 --> 10:39.810
NAH, I CAN'T DO IT.

10:39.810 --> 10:41.221
COME ON, I NEED TO LOG
MORE E.N.T. HOURS.

10:41.221 --> 10:43.433
AND HOW IS THAT
MY PROBLEM?

10:43.433 --> 10:45.475
[ STAMMERS ]

10:45.475 --> 10:47.938
[ MOUSE CLICKS ]

10:47.938 --> 10:49.359
LOOK AT THIS.

10:49.359 --> 10:50.941
DANNY'S
IN FULL-BLOWN CHOLANGITIS.

10:50.941 --> 10:52.072
WHAT WAS THAT
WITH DANNY?

10:52.072 --> 10:53.734
WHY WOULD YOU BRING UP
THAT SURGERY

10:53.734 --> 10:55.575
WITHOUT TALKING ABOUT IT
WITH ME FIRST?

10:55.575 --> 10:57.197
YOU BROUGHT ME ON AS A CONSULT
FOR MY OPINION.

10:57.197 --> 10:58.368
I WAS GIVING YOU
MY OPINION.

10:58.368 --> 10:59.830
HE'S BARELY ABLE TO
KEEP HIS BLOOD CLOTTING.

10:59.830 --> 11:01.451
YOU REALLY THINK HE'S GONNA
SURVIVE A SURGERY THAT BIG?

11:01.451 --> 11:03.043
I THOUGHT THAT'S WHY
YOU BROUGHT ME ON,

11:03.043 --> 11:04.204
BECAUSE YOU WANTED
SOME NEW IDEAS.

11:04.204 --> 11:05.665
HAVE YOU EVEN DONE
THIS PROCEDURE BEFORE?

11:05.665 --> 11:07.708
YOU CAME TO ME.
YOU BROUGHT THIS CASE TO ME.

11:07.708 --> 11:08.709
FOR YOUR HELP.

11:08.709 --> 11:09.960
SO THEN LISTEN TO ME.

11:12.172 --> 11:13.213
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE,
MER?

11:14.294 --> 11:16.006
NOTHING'S GOING ON.

11:16.006 --> 11:18.849
WOULD YOU RATHER HIM SIT AROUND
AND WAIT FOR A LIVER AND DIE

11:18.849 --> 11:20.851
OR LET ME TRY A SURGERY
I KNOW I CAN HANDLE?

11:20.851 --> 11:22.933
WHAT'S THE DEAL HERE?
IS THIS ABOUT YOUR STREAK?

11:22.933 --> 11:24.644
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
THEN WHAT?

11:24.644 --> 11:27.147
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?
WHAT'S YOUR DEAL TODAY?

11:27.147 --> 11:30.360
NOTHING. NO DEAL.
I HAVE NO DEAL.

11:32.072 --> 11:33.984
[ SIGHS ]

11:36.026 --> 11:40.410
WHAT IN THE WORLD LED YOU
TO DEVELOP THIS TECHNIQUE?

11:40.410 --> 11:42.202
IT WAS FOR A LITTLE SIDE HOBBY
OF MINE.

11:42.202 --> 11:43.203
WHICH IS?

11:43.203 --> 11:45.996
I WANT TO CURE AUTISM.

11:45.996 --> 11:47.878
THAT'S AMBITIOUS
FOR A FELLOW.

11:47.878 --> 11:48.919
HMM.

11:48.919 --> 11:51.291
WHAT MADE YOU DECIDE
TO TACKLE AUTISM?

11:51.291 --> 11:54.004
1 IN 68 KIDS
ISN'T ENOUGH?

11:54.004 --> 11:56.096
USUALLY IT COMES DOWN
TO JUST ONE.

11:58.218 --> 11:59.930
MY LITTLE SISTER.

11:59.930 --> 12:01.551
AH.

12:01.551 --> 12:05.435
I JUST ALWAYS WONDERED
WHAT SHE WAS THINKING.

12:09.770 --> 12:11.111
I HOPE YOU FIND THAT OUT.

12:11.111 --> 12:13.443
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:27.037 --> 12:28.999
[ MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

12:33.173 --> 12:35.175
HEY, WHY DIDN'T YOU
ANSWER MY TEXT?

12:35.175 --> 12:37.217
'CAUSE I WAS WORKING.
[ SIGHS ]

12:37.217 --> 12:39.549
SO?
SO WHAT?

12:39.549 --> 12:42.142
HOW IS MEREDITH?
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

12:42.142 --> 12:44.184
I KNOW SHE'S BEING AN ASS,

12:44.184 --> 12:45.936
PUSHING A RISKY SURGERY
ON MY PATIENT.

12:45.936 --> 12:47.227
SHE'S ON A STREAK.
GO FOR IT.

12:47.227 --> 12:49.019
WHO WAS THE WOMAN
ON DEREK'S PHONE?
I DON'T KNOW.

12:49.019 --> 12:51.151
SHE SAID NOTHING?
YESTERDAY, SHE COULDN'T
STOP TALKING ABOUT IT.

12:51.151 --> 12:52.772
ALL I KNOW IS DEREK
CAME HOME LAST NIGHT.

12:52.772 --> 12:54.524
[ GASPS ]
NO.

12:54.524 --> 12:55.605
CRAP.

12:55.605 --> 12:57.487
CRAP? WHY CRAP?

12:57.487 --> 13:00.570
A WOMAN ANSWERS HIS PHONE,
HE IMMEDIATELY GETS ON A PLANE

13:00.570 --> 13:02.863
AND SHOWS UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.

13:02.863 --> 13:05.365
HE'S HERE TO APOLOGIZE.

13:05.365 --> 13:07.787
BECAUSE HE HAS SOMETHING
TO APOLOGIZE FOR.

13:07.787 --> 13:10.120
[ SIGHS ]

13:10.120 --> 13:11.711
CRAP.

13:11.711 --> 13:14.004
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

13:14.004 --> 13:16.376
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

13:16.376 --> 13:19.799
Mrs. Hunt, I know this is hard,
but I need you to not move.

13:19.799 --> 13:21.842
I THINK I MIGHT BE DONE.
AM I DONE?

13:21.842 --> 13:25.015
Not quite yet.
Try focusing on your breathing.

13:26.766 --> 13:28.929
[ INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY ]

13:28.929 --> 13:31.021
I'M NOT USUALLY LIKE THIS.

13:31.021 --> 13:33.483
I WAS IN THE MILITARY.
I SERVED IN VIETNAM.

13:33.483 --> 13:36.486
I DON'T PANIC.
I THINK I'M JUST UPSET.

13:36.486 --> 13:38.528
Well,
you did have quite a fall.

13:38.528 --> 13:41.071
NOT ABOUT THE FALL.
ABOUT OWEN.

13:41.071 --> 13:44.995
I DIDN'T MEAN FOR HIM
TO FIND OUT LIKE THIS.

13:44.995 --> 13:48.658
HE HAS A RIGHT TO BE
A LITTLE SURPRISED...

13:48.658 --> 13:50.080
SHOCKED.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.161
BUT HOW DOES HE THINK I FEEL?

13:51.161 --> 13:55.085
A GUY LIKE JOHN CHASING
AFTER A FOSSIL LIKE ME.

13:55.085 --> 13:59.799
IT WAS WEEKS BEFORE I EVEN
REALIZED HE WAS DATING ME.

13:59.799 --> 14:01.461
AND THEN,
ONE NIGHT HE KISSED ME,

14:01.461 --> 14:03.553
AND...

14:03.553 --> 14:05.926
I'M NOT STUPID.

14:05.926 --> 14:08.468
I KNOW HOW WE MUST LOOK
TOGETHER.

14:08.468 --> 14:10.600
I KNOW WHAT PEOPLE
MUST THINK OF US.

14:10.600 --> 14:15.025
"HE'S CONNING HER.
SHE'S BUYING HIM.

14:15.025 --> 14:16.736
IT'S A JOKE."

14:16.736 --> 14:18.818
IT'S WHAT I'D THINK.

14:20.190 --> 14:22.782
BUT THEN HE KISSED ME.

14:24.364 --> 14:27.247
AND WHEN HE KISSED ME...

14:27.247 --> 14:30.250
WE WERE EXACTLY THE SAME AGE.

14:32.042 --> 14:35.085
ALL THOSE YEARS BETWEEN US
DISAPPEARED.

14:35.085 --> 14:38.298
JOHN ALWAYS SAYS, "EV,

14:38.298 --> 14:41.711
THERE'S NO DIFFERENCE BETWEEN US
EXCEPT A BUNCH OF YEARS.

14:41.711 --> 14:45.175
AND, FRANKLY, THEY'RE YEARS
I WISH I'D SPENT WITH YOU."

14:45.175 --> 14:48.888
OWEN'S ALWAYS WORRIED
THAT I'M LONELY.

14:48.888 --> 14:53.183
HIS DAD DIED 32 YEARS AGO,
SO HE WORRIES.

14:53.183 --> 14:54.935
BUT I'M NOT LONELY.

14:54.935 --> 14:58.068
[ DOOR OPENS ]
I'M HAVING THE TIME OF MY LIFE.

15:01.021 --> 15:02.732
AM I DONE?

15:02.732 --> 15:05.195
IN ORDER FOR ME
TO GET A CLEAN C.T. SCAN,

15:05.195 --> 15:08.078
I NEED FOR YOU TO BE PERFECTLY
STILL, WHICH MEANS...

15:08.078 --> 15:09.029
NO TALKING.

15:09.029 --> 15:11.241
NO TALKING.

15:11.241 --> 15:13.163
JOHN SOUNDS AMAZING.

15:13.163 --> 15:14.454
DOESN'T HE?

15:14.454 --> 15:17.297
IT WOULD BE SO MUCH EASIER
IF HE WERE MY AGE.

15:17.297 --> 15:21.131
BUT I GOT TO TELL YOU, IT'S
SO MUCH NICER THAT HE ISN'T.

15:21.131 --> 15:23.543
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:25.045 --> 15:26.756
[ WHIRRING ]

15:26.756 --> 15:28.428
OH, GOD.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.260
Jo: I KNOW
IT'S A LITTLE UNCOMFORTABLE,

15:30.260 --> 15:32.762
BUT WE CAN JUST GET A GOOD LOOK
AT WHAT'S GOING ON INSIDE.

15:32.762 --> 15:34.224
PLEASE DON'T FIND A TUMOR.

15:34.224 --> 15:36.436
NO, LOOKS GOOD.

15:36.436 --> 15:38.648
YOUR TISSUES LOOK HEALTHY.

15:40.020 --> 15:42.232
AAH!
AAH!

15:42.232 --> 15:44.154
[ GASPS ]

15:44.154 --> 15:45.655
WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:45.655 --> 15:46.987
NOTHING!

15:46.987 --> 15:48.528
I TOLD YOU TO PAGE ME
IF YOU HAD SOMETHING COOL.

15:48.528 --> 15:50.830
OH, IT'S NOT. SORRY.
NO, IT'S JUST A --

15:50.830 --> 15:52.622
IT'S JUST
ANOTHER NEUROTIC LADY

15:52.622 --> 15:55.035
WHO THOUGHT HER HEADACHE
WAS A BRAIN TUMOR.

15:55.035 --> 15:57.957
SO LOTS OF, UH, IBUPROFEN
AND HAND-HOLDING IN HERE.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.709
YOU SHOULD --
YOU SHOULD GO.

15:59.709 --> 16:02.172
FIND SOMETHING
WORTH YOUR HOURS.

16:06.086 --> 16:09.349
WHAT WAS THAT?
WHAT WAS THAT?!

16:09.349 --> 16:13.513
IT'S SOME KIND OF CRITTER.

16:13.513 --> 16:15.015
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "CRITTER"?

16:15.015 --> 16:16.726
IT'S ALIVE?
SOMETHING'S LIVING IN MY FACE?

16:16.726 --> 16:19.439
IT'S USING YOUR SINUS CAVITIES
TO MOVE AROUND.

16:19.439 --> 16:21.401
OH, MY GOD! I DON'T CARE!
JUST GET IT OUT!

16:21.401 --> 16:23.563
[ SOBS ]

16:25.405 --> 16:27.157
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

16:27.157 --> 16:28.868
HANG ON, ALL RIGHT?
HANG ON.

16:28.868 --> 16:30.280
LET ME PUT THIS MASK
ON YOU.

16:30.280 --> 16:31.821
Meredith:
START HIM ON AN ALBUMIN DRIP.

16:31.821 --> 16:35.035
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

16:35.035 --> 16:37.117
I WANT THE SURGERY.

16:37.117 --> 16:39.539
DANNY, WE WENT OVER THIS.
NO.

16:39.539 --> 16:42.292
I WANT THE SURGERY!

16:42.292 --> 16:43.793
DR. KAREV
IS GONNA DRAIN THE FLUID,

16:43.793 --> 16:45.085
AND YOU'RE GONNA
FEEL BETTER.

16:45.085 --> 16:46.256
NO! I WON'T!

16:46.256 --> 16:49.259
I CAN'T KEEP DOING THIS.
I WANT THE SURGERY.

16:49.259 --> 16:51.261
IT'S REALLY RISKY.
YOUR BODY'S VERY WEAK.

16:51.261 --> 16:52.552
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

16:52.552 --> 16:54.094
YES, I DO!

16:54.094 --> 16:56.846
I-I CAN'T GO OUT
LIKE THIS,

16:56.846 --> 16:59.099
SITTING IN SOME HOSPITAL BED,
WAITING,

16:59.099 --> 17:01.641
PROPPED UP
WITH MY SPECIAL PILLOWS,

17:01.641 --> 17:04.774
STARING AT CRAP
THAT DOESN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

17:04.774 --> 17:07.357
SOME HOCKEY PUCK YOU GOT SIGNED
FOR ME OUT OF PITY,

17:07.357 --> 17:11.361
PICTURES OF OUR DEAD PARENTS
WHO WOULD HAVE KNOWN BETTER

17:11.361 --> 17:14.154
THAN TO JUST LET ME SIT HERE
AND ROT.

17:14.154 --> 17:15.955
ALL RIGHT, HEY, DANNY.
IT'S FINE.

17:15.955 --> 17:18.037
NO, IT'S NOT.

17:18.037 --> 17:20.500
IT'S MY LIFE.
IT'S MY CHOICE.

17:21.711 --> 17:25.125
DR. GREY, I WANT THE SURGERY,
AND I WANT IT TODAY.

17:25.125 --> 17:27.217
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

17:30.590 --> 17:33.763
KATHY, HE'S HURTING RIGHT NOW,
ALL RIGHT?

17:33.763 --> 17:35.014
ONCE HE FEELS BETTER --

17:35.014 --> 17:37.437
WILL HE FEEL BETTER?

17:37.437 --> 17:39.639
I MEAN, HE'S RIGHT.
IT IS HIS LIFE.

17:39.639 --> 17:42.142
HE HAS SO LITTLE CONTROL
OVER ANYTHING ELSE,

17:42.142 --> 17:43.353
BUT HE'S ALMOST 18.

17:43.353 --> 17:46.486
HE SHOULD GET A SAY IN WHAT
HE DOES IN HIS LIFE, RIGHT?

17:46.486 --> 17:48.738
THAT'S WHAT HE WANTS.

17:48.738 --> 17:52.192
I MEAN, HE JUST WANTS TO GO TO
GAMES AND HANG OUT WITH GIRLS

17:52.192 --> 17:56.746
AND JUNK OUT ON POPCORN
WITH HIS FRIENDS AT THE MOVIES.

17:56.746 --> 17:59.329
HE'S MISERABLE
AND TERRIFIED.

17:59.329 --> 18:01.251
AND I DON'T BLAME HIM.

18:01.251 --> 18:04.204
JUST -- I'LL GIVE CONSENT.
JUST DO THE SURGERY.

18:04.204 --> 18:05.375
ABSOLUTELY.

18:05.375 --> 18:07.417
YOU'RE STILL HIS GUARDIAN.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

18:07.417 --> 18:09.589
JUST TELL ME THAT
IT'S GOING TO WORK.

18:09.589 --> 18:13.843
I SPENT MY ENTIRE ADULT LIFE
TAKING CARE OF HIM.

18:13.843 --> 18:17.177
NOW HE WANTS A LIFE,
BUT HE'S MY LIFE.

18:17.177 --> 18:20.270
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO
WITHOUT HIM.

18:20.270 --> 18:22.142
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

18:35.195 --> 18:38.037
[ GASPS ]

18:38.868 --> 18:40.500
RENEE?
OH!

18:40.500 --> 18:42.202
OH, GOD.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

18:42.202 --> 18:43.623
YOU OKAY?

18:43.623 --> 18:44.954
YEAH, I'M JUST, UH --

18:44.954 --> 18:46.626
I'M SORRY.
I-I BROKE A CUP.

18:46.626 --> 18:49.128
I'LL REPLACE IT.
I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT THE CUP.

18:49.128 --> 18:51.881
I'M FINE. I'M SORRY.
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

18:51.881 --> 18:54.674
DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT?

18:54.674 --> 18:56.015
[ SIGHS ]

18:57.967 --> 19:02.101
I'VE BEEN MEASURING
LEVELS OF ACTIVITY

19:02.101 --> 19:04.604
AND INHIBITORY CELLS
IN VPA RAT BRAINS.

19:04.604 --> 19:07.146
FOR MONTHS, I'VE BEEN PATCHING
AND PATCHING --

19:07.146 --> 19:09.399
FOR MORE THAN A YEAR,
ACTUALLY.
MM-HMM.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.821
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR ABNORMALITIES,

19:11.821 --> 19:13.653
AND NOTHING SHOWS UP.

19:13.653 --> 19:15.154
NOTHING.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.947
I'M WASTING MY TIME.

19:17.947 --> 19:20.660
DO YOU KNOW WHY
YOU FEEL LIKE THAT?

19:20.660 --> 19:22.992
IT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE CLOSE.

19:22.992 --> 19:25.995
YOU'RE VERY CLOSE
TO A BREAKTHROUGH.

19:25.995 --> 19:28.288
I'VE BEEN THERE.
IT'S TEDIOUS.

19:28.288 --> 19:31.251
IT TAKES PATIENCE
AND CONCENTRATION.

19:31.251 --> 19:34.003
AND YOU WANT IT.
YOU WANT A BREAKTHROUGH SO BAD

19:34.003 --> 19:36.055
THAT YOU HAVE TO
BREAK SOMETHING.

19:36.055 --> 19:37.597
I-I'LL REPLACE THE CUP.
I'M --

19:37.597 --> 19:40.220
STOP TALKING
ABOUT THE CUP.

19:40.220 --> 19:42.181
KEEP GOING.

19:42.181 --> 19:44.854
YOU'RE RIGHT AT THE LINE.

19:44.854 --> 19:47.106
YOU'RE GONNA CROSS IT.

19:48.978 --> 19:51.861
DON'T STOP.

19:59.909 --> 20:01.160
YOU SHOULD GET SOME SLEEP.

20:02.322 --> 20:04.534
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

20:04.534 --> 20:07.126
I'LL TRY.

20:07.126 --> 20:09.379
[ SIGHS ]

20:17.677 --> 20:21.140
HEY, SO, I SPOKE TO DR. WEBBER.
YOUR C.T. RESULTS CAME BACK.

20:21.140 --> 20:23.102
YOU HAVE
A MILD HEAD CONTUSION,

20:23.102 --> 20:25.144
SO THEY'RE GONNA KEEP AN EYE
ON IT OVERNIGHT.

20:25.144 --> 20:27.847
I SUPPOSE
YOU HAVE QUESTIONS.

20:27.847 --> 20:29.188
NO.

20:29.188 --> 20:31.691
UM [CLEARS THROAT]
I BROUGHT YOU SOME, UH, PANT--

20:31.691 --> 20:37.026
UH, SOME LADIES' UNDERTHINGS
AND, UH [CLEARS THROAT] SOCKS

20:37.026 --> 20:40.029
IN CASE YOUR, YOU KNOW --
YOUR FEET GET COLD.

20:40.029 --> 20:42.362
PATIENTS ARE ALWAYS TELLING ME
THAT THEIR FEET GET COLD,

20:42.362 --> 20:44.324
SO I THOUGHT "SOCKS."

20:44.324 --> 20:47.036
I SPENT YOUR WHOLE CHILDHOOD
TELLING YOU TO BE SURE

20:47.036 --> 20:49.168
YOU HAD CLEAN SOCKS
AND UNDERWEAR ON

20:49.168 --> 20:51.040
IN CASE
YOU WERE IN AN ACCIDENT.

20:51.040 --> 20:52.131
HERE I AM.

20:52.131 --> 20:54.003
NO SOCKS, NO UNDERWEAR.

20:55.295 --> 20:57.427
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

20:59.639 --> 21:01.641
OWEN, ASK.

21:02.842 --> 21:04.644
I-IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS.
I DON'T NEED TO --

21:04.644 --> 21:06.095
WE MET
IN A WRITER'S GROUP.

21:06.095 --> 21:08.648
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WROTE.

21:08.648 --> 21:10.560
JUST STORIES.

21:10.560 --> 21:13.523
LITTLE THINGS
ABOUT MY TIME IN THE SERVICE.

21:13.523 --> 21:15.605
JOHN LIKED THEM.

21:15.605 --> 21:19.028
ONE NIGHT, WE STAYED LATE
TALKING ABOUT MY STORIES,

21:19.028 --> 21:20.990
AND HE SHARED SOME OF HIS.

21:20.990 --> 21:23.363
HE -- HE DID A STINT
IN THE NAVY.

21:23.363 --> 21:26.075
AND AFTER A WHILE,

21:26.075 --> 21:30.169
WE REALIZED WE WERE
THE ONLY ONES STILL AROUND.

21:31.621 --> 21:35.124
HE ASKED IF I WANTED TO
GO FOR SOME COFFEE

21:35.124 --> 21:37.046
AND KEEP
THE CONVERSATION GOING.

21:37.046 --> 21:38.418
I DID.

21:41.551 --> 21:43.803
THAT WAS SIX MONTHS AGO.

21:43.803 --> 21:48.348
AND SOMEHOW WE'VE NEVER
RUN OUT OF THINGS TO TALK ABOUT.

21:51.060 --> 21:54.313
SO, THAT'S IT?
JUST COFFEE AND CONVERSATION?

21:54.313 --> 21:56.896
DO YOU REALLY WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER'S SEX LIFE?

21:56.896 --> 21:58.738
OKAY, UM...

21:58.738 --> 22:03.242
OWEN, DOES IT MATTER
THAT HE'S NOT WHAT YOU PICTURED?

22:03.242 --> 22:06.115
YES, IT MATTERS, 'CAUSE
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG HERE.

22:06.115 --> 22:07.116
[ SIGHS ]

22:07.116 --> 22:09.369
HE'S HALF YOUR AGE.
HE'S YOUNGER THAN I AM.

22:11.000 --> 22:14.253
MOM,
I THINK HE'S USING YOU.

22:14.253 --> 22:16.586
FOR WHAT? FOR SEX?

22:16.586 --> 22:17.837
WELL, GOD BLESS HIM.

22:17.837 --> 22:19.919
STOP IT.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

22:19.919 --> 22:21.881
FOR MONEY.
YOUR PENSION, MAYBE.

22:21.881 --> 22:23.302
THAT'S WHAT THESE GUYS DO.

22:23.302 --> 22:26.015
THEY -- THEY PREY
ON OLDER PEOPLE.

22:26.015 --> 22:29.138
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "THESE GUYS"?
JOHN'S NOT "THESE GUYS."

22:29.138 --> 22:31.350
THERE'S NO WAY A MAN LIKE THAT
COULD...

22:34.434 --> 22:36.476
COULD LOVE ME?

22:39.819 --> 22:42.902
IS THAT WHAT
YOU WERE GONNA SAY?

22:42.902 --> 22:46.986
THERE'S NO WAY A MAN LIKE THAT
COULD LOVE ME.

22:46.986 --> 22:49.158
MOM.

22:49.158 --> 22:50.540
JUST THINK ABOUT IT.

22:53.292 --> 22:59.128
FOR A MOMENT, PUT YOUR HEART
ASIDE AND TRY TO THINK ABOUT IT.

22:59.128 --> 23:01.260
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME
RIGHT AWAY.

23:01.260 --> 23:03.553
I WOULD HAVE NEVER LET THIS GUY
DO THIS TO YOU.

23:03.553 --> 23:04.804
IT'S NOT RIGHT.

23:04.804 --> 23:06.466
IT FEELS RIGHT.

23:06.466 --> 23:08.598
[ SIGHS ]

23:10.179 --> 23:11.681
I WANT YOU TO GO.

23:11.681 --> 23:13.182
MOM.

23:13.182 --> 23:16.145
I DON'T WANT TO SEE ANYONE
MAKE A FOOL OUT OF YOU.

23:16.145 --> 23:18.227
AND I WON'T LET ANYBODY
HURT YOU.

23:18.227 --> 23:20.399
PLEASE.

23:26.365 --> 23:29.198
[ CRYING ]

23:31.160 --> 23:32.832
[ SIGHS ]

23:32.832 --> 23:36.205
I LIKE YOUR MOM.
SHE'S FUNNY AND SMART.

23:36.205 --> 23:37.707
I MEAN, I'M NOT SURPRISED.
IS THERE A POINT?

23:39.298 --> 23:43.803
OWEN, IF IT WERE MY MOM,
I WOULD BE THROWN, TOO,

23:43.803 --> 23:45.004
BUT FROM TALKING TO HER,

23:45.004 --> 23:46.806
IT SEEMS LIKE
THEY'RE REALLY IN LOVE.

23:46.806 --> 23:48.347
[ SCOFFS ] YOU SPENT 15 MINUTES
LISTENING TO HER,

23:48.347 --> 23:49.889
AND YOU HAVE THIS WHOLE THING
FIGURED OUT.

23:49.889 --> 23:51.010
I KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT THIS GUY.

23:51.010 --> 23:52.181
YOU DON'T KNOW MY MOTHER,

23:52.181 --> 23:53.012
SO PLEASE JUST STAY
THE HELL OUT OF IT.

23:59.358 --> 24:01.150
[ SIGHS ]

24:03.062 --> 24:05.154
WE WENT TO
THIS BEAUTIFUL LAKE...

24:05.154 --> 24:06.365
Jo: Shh. DON'T SPEAK.

24:06.365 --> 24:07.487
...WITH THESE WATERFALLS.

24:07.487 --> 24:09.068
YOU'LL SCARE HIM AWAY.

24:09.068 --> 24:12.742
EVERYONE ON MY TOUR WAS JUMPING
OFF THIS BIG, HIGH LEDGE

24:12.742 --> 24:14.243
INTO THE LAKE.

24:14.243 --> 24:17.166
I WAS SO TERRIFIED TO DO IT,
BUT IT WAS LIKE

24:17.166 --> 24:20.670
THE BIG, HIGH POINT OF THE TRIP
FOR THEM.

24:20.670 --> 24:22.341
I DIDN'T WANT TO BE THE ONLY ONE
WHO DIDN'T GO.

24:22.341 --> 24:25.795
I DIDN'T WANT TO MISS OUT
ON THE HIGH POINT.

24:25.795 --> 24:29.138
I'M SO GLAD I JUMPED.
IT WAS EXHILARATING.

24:29.138 --> 24:31.891
AMAZING.
IT CHANGED ME FOREVER.

24:31.891 --> 24:32.932
PLEASE STOP TALKING.

24:35.855 --> 24:38.477
DO YOU THINK THAT'S WHEN
I GOT THIS THING IN ME?

24:39.729 --> 24:43.312
ANDREA, DON'T MOVE.

24:43.312 --> 24:47.106
COME TO MAMA.

24:47.106 --> 24:49.108
OH, NO!
STOP, STOP, STOP!

24:49.108 --> 24:51.030
IT'S GRABBING.
IT'S GRABBING.
JUST A LITTLE MORE.
JUST A LITTLE --

24:51.030 --> 24:52.161
STOP IT! [ GASPS ]

24:52.161 --> 24:54.874
OH, MY GOD.
I'M SO SORRY.

24:56.035 --> 24:58.117
OKAY.

24:58.117 --> 25:01.080
WE'RE GONNA TAKE
A LITTLE BREAK.

25:01.080 --> 25:02.421
THEN WE'LL TRY AGAIN.

25:02.421 --> 25:04.083
I'M NOT DOING THAT AGAIN.

25:04.083 --> 25:06.465
I'M NOT DOING IT.

25:06.465 --> 25:09.629
Jackson:
WE'LL NEED TO BE VERY CAREFUL
WHEN CONNECTING THE GRAFT

25:09.629 --> 25:11.721
TO THE POSTERIOR
AURICULAR ARTERY.

25:11.721 --> 25:15.725
AND...THERE.

25:15.725 --> 25:17.226
SCISSORS, PLEASE.

25:32.822 --> 25:36.075
UH, HELLO, DR. BAILEY.

25:36.075 --> 25:37.496
BRIBERY, EDWARDS?

25:37.496 --> 25:40.039
YOU THINK BRIBERY IS AN
APPROPRIATE STANDARD OF PRACTICE

25:40.039 --> 25:41.831
IN THIS HOSPITAL,
BRIBING FOR SURGERIES?

25:41.831 --> 25:43.212
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

25:43.212 --> 25:45.464
YOU TRIED TO BRIBE YOUR WAY
ONTO THAT SURGERY DOWN THERE.

25:45.464 --> 25:47.046
WARREN.

25:47.046 --> 25:48.718
SLEEPING WITH THE ENEMY.

25:48.718 --> 25:51.300
YOU DEMEAN YOURSELF,
AND YOU DEMEAN MEDICINE.

25:51.300 --> 25:52.511
I'M SORRY.

25:52.511 --> 25:54.844
AND IT DOESN'T MATTER, ANYWAY.
IT DIDN'T WORK.

25:54.844 --> 25:58.387
$50? [ SCOFFS ]

25:58.387 --> 26:00.179
$50.

26:00.179 --> 26:02.311
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
A FULL EAR REPLANTATION

26:02.311 --> 26:04.103
WOULD HAVE GONE FOR
IN MY DAY?

26:04.103 --> 26:05.354
$100, EASY.

26:05.354 --> 26:09.148
$120, EVEN,
PLUS TWO WEEKS OF NIGHT CALL.

26:09.148 --> 26:10.189
YOU ADD IN INFLATION,

26:10.189 --> 26:12.742
YOU SHOULD HAVE OFFERED HIM
$175, AT LEAST.

26:12.742 --> 26:14.493
$50.

26:16.956 --> 26:20.119
WE CAN'T EVEN GO TO DINNER
FOR $50.

26:22.001 --> 26:24.503
GELFOAM, PLEASE.
I NEED MORE RETRACTION.

26:24.503 --> 26:26.295
ANY MORE, AND WE'LL NEED TO
EXTEND THE INCISION.

26:26.295 --> 26:28.207
WELL, THEN WE'LL EXTEND
THE INCISION.

26:28.207 --> 26:30.209
I NEED BETTER VISUALIZATION
OF THE BILE DUCT.

26:30.209 --> 26:32.171
HIS HEPATIC VEINS ARE BLEEDING.
HIS LIVER'S TOO SCARRED.

26:32.171 --> 26:34.013
WE NEED TO STOP,
GIVE HIM EXTRA CLOTTING FACTORS.

26:34.013 --> 26:36.175
WE CAN'T STOP.
I TOLD YOU
IT WAS A BAD IDEA.

26:36.175 --> 26:38.387
HIS BODY CAN'T TAKE IT.
HE'S ALREADY DETERIORATING.

26:38.387 --> 26:39.558
LET'S PACK HIM AND GET OUT.

26:39.558 --> 26:41.140
WE CAN'T CLOSE HIM NOW.
HE WILL DIE.

26:41.140 --> 26:42.271
HE'LL BE DEAD IN A WEEK.

26:42.271 --> 26:44.183
HOW LONG HAS HE BEEN ON
THE TRANSPLANT LIST?

26:44.183 --> 26:46.816
WILL HE GET A LIVER
THIS WEEK?

26:48.818 --> 26:51.150
I COULD DO A HEPATICO-J
TO DECOMPRESS THE LIVER.

26:51.150 --> 26:53.152
THAT'S CRAZY.
IT'LL NEVER WORK.
IT'S A CHANCE.

26:53.152 --> 26:55.074
I DIDN'T ASK YOU FOR A CHANCE.
I ASKED YOU FOR AN OPINION.

26:55.074 --> 26:56.786
WHICH I GAVE YOU,
WHICH I'M GIVING YOU NOW,

26:56.786 --> 26:58.407
WHICH YOU REFUSE
TO LISTEN TO.

26:58.407 --> 27:01.040
YOU HIJACKED MY PATIENT
TO PERFORM A PROCEDURE
THAT COULD KILL HIM.

27:01.040 --> 27:04.043
IF YOU DON'T LIKE MY SURGICAL
PLAN, YOU ARE FREE TO LEAVE.
WHAT THE HELL
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

27:04.043 --> 27:06.125
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
DAMN IT.
HE'S DROPPING HIS PRESSURE.

27:06.125 --> 27:08.007
I'M PUTTING A SHUNT IN
FROM THE SPLENIC TO THE IVC.

27:08.007 --> 27:09.378
THE ANASTOMOSIS
IS NOT GONNA HOLD.

27:09.378 --> 27:11.300
IT'S THE ONLY WAY.
RIGHT ANGLE.

27:18.718 --> 27:20.930
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

27:23.973 --> 27:25.765
HELLO?

27:25.765 --> 27:26.686
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
RIGHT NOW?

27:26.686 --> 27:30.189
I WAS [CLEARS THROAT]

27:30.189 --> 27:31.190
It's 1:00 a.m.

27:31.190 --> 27:32.481
HOW SOON CAN YOU
BE AT THE LAB?

27:35.364 --> 27:37.076
I COULDN'T STOP THINKING
ABOUT YOUR RESEARCH.

27:37.076 --> 27:39.989
YOU'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT MY RESEARCH?

27:39.989 --> 27:42.371
COME HERE. COME ON.
LET ME SHOW YOU. LOOK.

27:46.045 --> 27:47.336
OH, MY GOD.

27:47.336 --> 27:48.958
YEAH, I KNOW.
I TOLD YOU.

27:48.958 --> 27:51.130
IT'S ALL ABOUT
THE EXCITATORY PATHWAYS.

27:52.001 --> 27:53.753
HERE, LOOK.

27:53.753 --> 27:54.884
SEE?

27:54.884 --> 27:56.135
YEAH.

27:59.428 --> 28:02.391
YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE'S DROPPED
SINCE THE LAST CHECK.

28:02.391 --> 28:03.642
YOU FEELING OKAY?

28:03.642 --> 28:06.185
I FEEL LIKE I'M BEING MADE
TOO MUCH FUSS OVER

28:06.185 --> 28:07.727
'CAUSE MY SON'S THE BOSS.

28:07.727 --> 28:09.648
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

28:09.648 --> 28:12.361
OKAY, SO, UH,
THE CAT'S FED,

28:12.361 --> 28:14.443
UM, I GOT THE RECYCLING
DOWN TO THE CURB.

28:14.443 --> 28:15.815
I BROUGHT YOU SOME CLOTHES
AND STUFF.

28:15.815 --> 28:17.116
I COULDN'T FIND
YOUR JOURNAL,

28:17.116 --> 28:19.278
SO I JUST PICKED YOU UP A FRESH
ONE DOWN IN THE GIFT SHOP.

28:19.278 --> 28:21.240
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO
DO ALL THAT.

28:21.240 --> 28:24.163
HEY.

28:24.163 --> 28:26.325
HEY, ARE YOU --
ARE YOU OKAY?

28:26.325 --> 28:27.376
IS SHE OKAY?

28:28.918 --> 28:30.669
I'M FINE.

28:32.001 --> 28:34.253
YOU'VE VERY, VERY SWEET.

28:36.005 --> 28:37.676
BUT I DON'T THINK...

28:39.929 --> 28:42.681
WE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THIS.

28:42.681 --> 28:44.513
NOT ANYMORE.

28:44.513 --> 28:45.805
WHAT?

28:45.805 --> 28:48.147
YOU DON'T NEED THIS,
JOHN --

28:48.147 --> 28:50.559
A FRAIL, OLD WOMAN
WHO FALLS IN THE SHOWER.

28:50.559 --> 28:53.522
STOP IT. IS THIS --
IS THIS BECAUSE OWEN --

28:53.522 --> 28:56.195
HE'S MY SON.

28:56.195 --> 28:59.158
AND HE'S BEEN TO HELL
AND BACK.

28:59.158 --> 29:01.821
AND HE DOES EVERYTHING
FOR ME.

29:01.821 --> 29:03.162
AND IF HE FEELS
THAT IT ISN'T --

29:03.162 --> 29:04.283
HEY, HEY, EVELYN.

29:06.035 --> 29:08.537
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?

29:08.537 --> 29:10.169
OHH!

29:10.169 --> 29:11.580
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
WE NEED HELP IN HERE!

29:11.580 --> 29:13.712
OH! AAH! AAH! AAH!

29:13.712 --> 29:15.544
OKAY,
HER ABDOMEN'S RIGID.

29:15.544 --> 29:17.426
EVELYN.
STEP OUTSIDE, ALL RIGHT?

29:17.426 --> 29:18.838
BLOOD PRESSURE'S DROPPING
DRASTICALLY.

29:18.838 --> 29:20.179
SHE'S GOING INTO SHOCK.

29:20.179 --> 29:22.341
PAGE PIERCE,
AND GET OWEN HUNT.

29:23.642 --> 29:25.144
OH!

29:25.144 --> 29:26.806
I'M RIGHT HERE.

29:31.811 --> 29:33.022
SHUNT IS IN.

29:33.022 --> 29:34.193
BLEEDING
SEEMS UNDER CONTROL.

29:34.193 --> 29:36.065
YOU SEEM SURPRISED.
I'M GLAD IT WORKED.

29:36.065 --> 29:37.656
YOU'VE QUESTIONED
EVERY MOVE I'VE MADE.

29:37.656 --> 29:39.738
YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE?
I NEED YOU TO BELIEVE IN ME.

29:39.738 --> 29:40.950
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
CRAP, THERE'S --

29:40.950 --> 29:43.402
I SEE IT.
THE ANASTOMOSIS IS LEAKING.

29:43.402 --> 29:45.664
COME ON, DANNY.

29:45.664 --> 29:47.496
[ SUCTION SLURPING ]

29:48.667 --> 29:50.119
WHAT HAPPENED?!

29:50.119 --> 29:52.041
RUPTURED ABDOMINAL
AORTIC ANEURYSM.

29:52.041 --> 29:53.412
THE DIZZINESS,
THE BRUISING ON HER BACK --

29:53.412 --> 29:55.044
THEY MUST HAVE BEEN CAUSED
BY A SENTINEL BLEED.

29:55.044 --> 29:57.006
WHAT THE HELL, RICHARD?
HOW'D YOU NOT SEE THIS?

29:57.006 --> 29:58.717
HEY, ALL OF HER INJURIES
WERE CONSISTENT WITH HER FALL.

29:58.717 --> 30:00.219
NONE OF US WOULD HAVE THOUGHT
TO LOOK ANY FURTHER.

30:00.219 --> 30:01.680
I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED,
BUT WE HAVE HER.

30:03.262 --> 30:05.224
[ SIGHS ]

30:10.269 --> 30:12.691
[ SIGHS ]

30:20.109 --> 30:21.110
HEY.

30:21.110 --> 30:23.032
I NEED YOU TO TELL ME
WHY YOU'RE HERE.

30:23.032 --> 30:25.034
I'M GONNA GO.
SHE TOLD ME TO GO.

30:25.034 --> 30:26.535
GOOD. GO.
I WILL.

30:26.535 --> 30:29.408
BUT NOT UNTIL I KNOW
SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

30:29.408 --> 30:33.082
I KNOW SHE DOESN'T WANT ME,
AND THAT'S FINE.

30:33.082 --> 30:36.085
BUT I CAN'T JUST WALK AWAY
NOT KNOWING HOW SHE IS.

30:36.085 --> 30:38.257
I CAN'T JUST WALK AWAY
FROM...

30:38.257 --> 30:43.092
I KNOW SHE DOESN'T WANT ME,
BUT I WANT HER.

30:43.092 --> 30:47.096
I HAVE TO KNOW THAT SHE'S
OUT THERE IN THE WORLD OKAY.

30:47.096 --> 30:48.847
I CAN'T GO NOT KNOWING.

30:48.847 --> 30:51.100
SHE'LL NEVER EVEN KNOW
I WAS HERE.

30:51.100 --> 30:53.352
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY ANYTHING
TO HER.

30:53.352 --> 30:56.235
I'LL GO THE MOMENT
THAT I KNOW.

30:56.235 --> 31:02.401
BUT UNTIL THEN,
I AM SITTING HERE IN THIS CHAIR,

31:02.401 --> 31:05.114
UNTIL I KNOW
THAT EVELYN IS ALL RIGHT.

31:05.114 --> 31:08.697
♪ YOU CAN STILL SEE
WHERE THE WATER WAS ♪

31:10.199 --> 31:13.082
♪ IN A LINE AT THE TOP
OF THE CHIMNEY BRICKS ♪

31:15.374 --> 31:21.260
♪ SOMETIMES, SOMETHING SO BROKEN
CAN NEVER BE FIXED ♪
[ SIGHS ]

31:25.004 --> 31:30.269
♪ SO WE SAVED A FEW THINGS
THAT WERE SPARED ♪

31:30.269 --> 31:33.852
♪ AND BROUGHT IT TO THE GROUND ♪

31:35.184 --> 31:40.729
♪ 'CAUSE YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT
BETTER THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪

31:40.729 --> 31:42.861
[ SUCTION SLURPING ]

31:45.985 --> 31:50.909
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

31:50.909 --> 31:53.032
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

31:55.664 --> 32:01.090
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

32:02.171 --> 32:04.423
HEY. HE'S OKAY, RIGHT?
THE SURGERY WORKED?

32:04.423 --> 32:05.804
CAN I SEE HIM?

32:05.804 --> 32:09.308
♪ I DROVE PAST THE PLACE
WHERE WE USED TO LIVE ♪

32:09.308 --> 32:10.759
DR. GREY?

32:10.759 --> 32:13.932
♪ WHERE YOU SAID
YOU NEVER WANTED KIDS ♪

32:13.932 --> 32:16.935
KATHY, UM, I'M --

32:16.935 --> 32:19.938
♪ SOMETIMES, SOMETHING
SO BROKEN ♪
I'M SO SORRY.

32:19.938 --> 32:22.111
♪ CAN NEVER BE FIXED ♪
UM, I'M SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

32:22.111 --> 32:23.322
NO!

32:23.322 --> 32:25.194
[ SOBBING ]

32:25.194 --> 32:27.156
[ Sobbing ] OH, MY GOD.

32:27.156 --> 32:29.408
♪ I'M SLEEPING MORE
AND EATING AGAIN ♪
NO!

32:31.410 --> 32:34.994
♪ I'M STARTING OVER
LIKE A FACTORY TOWN ♪

32:36.375 --> 32:42.211
♪ AND YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER
THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

32:46.295 --> 32:50.589
♪ YOU ALWAYS
BUILD IT BETTER ♪
TELL ME THAT'S NOT --
YES.

32:50.589 --> 32:53.012
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
THE VPA CELLS ARE CONNECTING
ALMOST TWICE THE RATE

32:53.012 --> 32:54.593
OF NORMAL CELLS.

32:54.593 --> 32:57.146
THIS IS AMAZING!
MM-HMM.

32:57.146 --> 32:59.188
♪ YOU ALWAYS
BUILD IT BETTER ♪
YOU'RE AMAZING!
I COULD KISS YOU.

32:59.188 --> 33:01.360
UH..
UH, I MEAN, I WON'T.

33:01.360 --> 33:03.442
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
OBVIOUSLY I WON'T.
SORRY.

33:03.442 --> 33:06.445
BUT ALL THE WRONG TURNS
AND BRICK WALLS,

33:06.445 --> 33:09.028
AND FINDING THE ANSWER
IS SUCH A HIGH.

33:09.028 --> 33:10.029
HMM.

33:10.029 --> 33:11.870
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:23.832 --> 33:26.505
IT'S GETTING LATE.

33:26.505 --> 33:30.259
UM...I SHOULD GO.

33:30.259 --> 33:32.971
DO YOU HAVE TO?

33:36.935 --> 33:41.810
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪

33:41.810 --> 33:46.945
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪

33:46.945 --> 33:53.242
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER
THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪

33:53.242 --> 33:56.205
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

33:56.205 --> 33:57.326
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

33:57.326 --> 33:59.708
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪

33:59.708 --> 34:01.120
MEREDITH!

34:01.120 --> 34:02.791
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

34:02.791 --> 34:04.213
MER, STOP!

34:04.213 --> 34:05.164
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

34:05.164 --> 34:08.087
HE SHOULD HAVE LIVED.
HE COULDN'T.

34:08.087 --> 34:09.878
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪
YOU SAW HOW MESSED UP
HIS LIVER WAS.

34:09.878 --> 34:12.010
I SHOULD HAVE SAVED HIM.

34:12.010 --> 34:14.012
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
I COULD HAVE SAVED HIM IF YOU
WEREN'T BRINGING ME DOWN...

34:14.012 --> 34:16.095
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪
...WITH YOUR DOUBTING
AND SECOND-GUESSING
AND DISTRACTING ME.

34:16.095 --> 34:18.016
MER.
HE SHOULD HAVE LIVED.

34:18.016 --> 34:21.230
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪
HE SHOULD HAVE LIVED!
HE SHOULD HAVE LIVED.

34:21.230 --> 34:22.141
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
WHAT?

34:22.141 --> 34:24.233
STOP. GET OFF!
STOP IT!

34:24.233 --> 34:25.894
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪
COME ON. NO.

34:25.894 --> 34:27.025
I'M MAD AT YOU.
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

34:27.025 --> 34:28.947
I AM.
NO, YOU'RE MAD AT DEREK.

34:28.947 --> 34:31.029
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪
YOU WANT TO TAKE IT OUT ON ME,
GO ON.

34:31.029 --> 34:32.991
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
YOU WANT TO YELL AND HIT
AND SCREAM

34:32.991 --> 34:34.363
'CAUSE THINGS ARE HARD AT HOME,
OKAY.

34:34.363 --> 34:35.614
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪
YOU WANT TO BE A MESS,
BE A MESS.

34:35.614 --> 34:37.116
I DON'T CARE.
I CAN TAKE IT.

34:37.116 --> 34:39.248
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER ♪
BUT IN THAT O.R. --

34:39.248 --> 34:41.960
YOU ARE NOT A MESS IN THAT O.R.
YOU TRIED. WE BOTH DID.

34:41.960 --> 34:43.962
♪ THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪
YOU DIDN'T DO THIS.
YOU DIDN'T KILL THAT KID, OKAY?

34:43.962 --> 34:45.083
SO KEEP IT TOGETHER.

34:45.083 --> 34:50.088
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

34:50.088 --> 34:55.214
♪ YOU ALWAYS BUILD IT BETTER
THE SECOND TIME AROUND ♪

35:01.059 --> 35:02.351
[ SIGHS ]

35:02.351 --> 35:04.643
WE WERE ABLE TO REPAIR
HER ANEURYSM.

35:04.643 --> 35:06.275
SO SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY?
YEAH, THAT'S GOOD.

35:06.275 --> 35:09.818
SHE SHOULD RECOVERY NICELY.
THAT WAS ONE LUCKY FALL.

35:09.818 --> 35:12.401
IF HER ANEURYSM HAD RUPTURED
OUTSIDE OF THE HOSPITAL,

35:12.401 --> 35:13.822
SHE WOULDN'T HAVE MADE IT.

35:13.822 --> 35:14.993
ALL RIGHT.

35:14.993 --> 35:16.114
THANK YOU.

35:18.327 --> 35:20.739
[ SIGHS ]

35:20.739 --> 35:22.291
THANKS.

35:22.291 --> 35:23.912
MM.

35:23.912 --> 35:27.836
UH...TELL YOUR MOM
I SAID GOODBYE.

35:27.836 --> 35:29.047
OH.

35:30.799 --> 35:33.712
I ORDERED THIS BOOK THAT SHE'S
BEEN SEARCHING FOR FOREVER.

35:33.712 --> 35:36.215
IT WAS OUT OF PRINT. I FOUND IT.
I HAD IT SHIPPED.

35:36.215 --> 35:37.926
UH, IT ARRIVED YESTERDAY.

35:37.926 --> 35:40.018
UM, IT'S IN THIS
LITTLE BROWN PACKAGE

35:40.018 --> 35:41.810
ON THE TABLE
NEAR THE BLUE SOFA.

35:41.810 --> 35:43.021
WILL YOU MAKE SURE
SHE GETS IT?

35:43.021 --> 35:44.393
YEAH.

35:44.393 --> 35:46.064
THANKS.

35:47.606 --> 35:49.478
JOHN, WAIT.

35:56.195 --> 35:59.077
I TOLD YOU TO GO.

35:59.077 --> 36:03.332
YEAH, WELL, OWEN SUGGESTED
THAT YOU MIGHT BE FULL OF CRAP.

36:03.332 --> 36:05.244
HMM.
I ASKED HIM TO STICK AROUND.

36:05.244 --> 36:06.745
WE'VE BEEN TALKING.

36:10.128 --> 36:12.751
OH, GOD. I WISH YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO SEE ME LIKE THIS.

36:12.751 --> 36:13.962
I LOOK SO --

36:13.962 --> 36:15.133
Shh, shh, shh.

36:17.135 --> 36:19.258
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

36:29.017 --> 36:31.149
NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

36:31.149 --> 36:33.191
April: OKAY,
JUST RELAX, ANDREA.

36:33.191 --> 36:35.023
DR. WILSON SAID I COULD
HAVE A LOOK AT YOUR
LITTLE BUDDY THERE?

36:35.023 --> 36:36.024
NO.

36:36.024 --> 36:38.026
OKAY, I FEEL FOR YOU.
I DO.

36:38.026 --> 36:39.077
BUT YOU GOT TO LET US
YANK HIM OUT.

36:39.077 --> 36:40.909
WILSON!
BUT IT HURTS.

36:40.909 --> 36:42.120
I THINK HE HAS TEETH.

36:42.120 --> 36:44.663
I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED.

36:44.663 --> 36:47.786
HE IS, TOO.
HE DOESN'T WANT TO COME OUT.

36:47.786 --> 36:52.090
HE HAS FOUND THE PERFECT...
SAFE HOME.

36:52.090 --> 36:56.174
THE TISSUES IN YOUR SINUSES
ARE WARM AND DAMP AND COZY.

36:56.174 --> 37:00.469
BUT THEY'RE ALSO TASTY,
AND HE'S GONNA GET HUNGRY,

37:00.469 --> 37:02.931
AND THEN HE'S GONNA
START CHOMPING AWAY.

37:02.931 --> 37:05.053
AND THE MORE
HE CHOMPS THROUGH THEM,

37:05.053 --> 37:07.185
THE CLOSER HE'S GONNA GET
TO YOUR BRAIN.

37:07.185 --> 37:10.108
AND YOUR BRAIN --
OH, YOUR BRAIN.

37:10.108 --> 37:12.771
THAT'LL -- THAT'LL BE
LIKE CHRISTMAS DINNER.

37:12.771 --> 37:14.903
HE'S HERE. HE'S RIGHT HERE.
GET HIM OUT.

37:14.903 --> 37:16.615
OKAY, OKAY, ANDREA.
THIS IS WHAT I WANT YOU TO DO.

37:16.615 --> 37:18.817
I WANT YOU TO TAKE
A GREAT BIG SNIFF.

37:18.817 --> 37:21.119
WHAT? SNIFF IN?
NO WAY.

37:21.119 --> 37:23.121
H-HE'LL END UP SOMEWHERE
BEHIND MY EYEBALL.

37:23.121 --> 37:25.073
NO, HE WON'T.
YOUR SINUSES WILL CONTRACT.

37:25.073 --> 37:27.205
IT'LL HELP. I PROMISE.
READY? SNIFF.

37:27.205 --> 37:29.748
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

37:29.748 --> 37:30.999
[ WHIMPERS ]

37:34.002 --> 37:35.133
[ GASPS ]

37:35.133 --> 37:38.046
THERE YOU ARE,
YOU LITTLE BUGGER.

37:38.046 --> 37:39.137
OH, MY GOD.

37:39.137 --> 37:40.639
OH, MY GOD.
IT'S SO GROSS.

37:40.639 --> 37:42.721
AND HE WAS IN MY FACE.
WHAT IS IT?

37:42.721 --> 37:45.514
OH, IT'S A LEECH.
POOR LITTLE GUY.

37:45.514 --> 37:46.345
DO YOU WANT TO KEEP HIM?

37:47.386 --> 37:48.266
IF YOU DON'T, I WILL.

37:56.605 --> 37:58.106
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

37:58.106 --> 37:59.778
WHAT? WHAT IS THAT?

37:59.778 --> 38:04.703
I PULLED IT OUT
OF A LADY'S NOSE.

38:04.703 --> 38:07.115
THIS LITTLE SUCKER HAD ME
WORKING ON ONE SINGLE CASE

38:07.115 --> 38:08.497
ALL DAY.

38:08.497 --> 38:10.038
ALL DAY?

38:10.038 --> 38:11.620
ALL DAY.

38:11.620 --> 38:15.754
SO YOU JUST LOGGED SIX, SEVEN
UNINTERRUPTED HOURS OF TRAUMA

38:15.754 --> 38:17.125
WITHOUT EVEN TRYING,

38:17.125 --> 38:19.257
ALL BECAUSE OF A STUPID LEECH
UP SOMEONE'S STUPID NOSE?

38:19.257 --> 38:21.470
I THINK I'M GONNA
NAME HIM HERBIE.

38:21.470 --> 38:24.182
I'M GONNA PUT HERBIE
UP YOUR NOSE WHILE YOU SLEEP.

38:32.020 --> 38:33.311
[ HORNS HONKING ]

38:33.311 --> 38:35.103
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

38:35.103 --> 38:36.735
AMELIA. I AM SO...

38:36.735 --> 38:38.357
SORRY?

38:38.357 --> 38:41.199
FOR BEING SUCH A JACKASS?

38:41.199 --> 38:45.033
AND FOR HOW I SPOKE TO YOU.
I WAS OUT OF LINE.

38:45.033 --> 38:47.115
YOU THINK?

38:47.115 --> 38:48.947
I AM SORRY.

38:51.079 --> 38:52.160
GOOD.

38:53.211 --> 38:55.914
DON'T GO.
NOT LIKE THIS.

38:55.914 --> 38:58.046
[ SIGHS ]

38:58.046 --> 39:01.299
IT JUST TOOK ME
BY SURPRISE.

39:01.299 --> 39:03.341
[ SIGHS ]

39:03.341 --> 39:05.924
I-I'M NOT ALWAYS GOOD
WITH SURPRISES.

39:07.265 --> 39:08.967
ME EITHER.

39:08.967 --> 39:11.229
[ SIGHS ]

39:11.229 --> 39:13.311
MAYBE WE SHOULD
GET OVER THAT.

39:13.311 --> 39:16.234
WHEN WE GO WITHOUT CERTAIN
THINGS FOR LONG ENOUGH,

39:16.234 --> 39:19.738
IT'S EASY TO FORGET...

39:19.738 --> 39:22.821
JUST HOW MUCH WE NEED THEM.

39:28.036 --> 39:31.079
WE FORGET WHAT WE HAD ONCE.

39:32.160 --> 39:34.703
WE FORGET WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO LIVE WITH A THING...

39:37.205 --> 39:41.049
...NOT THAT WE NEED,
BUT THAT WE WANT.

39:41.049 --> 39:43.211
THE KIDS?

39:43.211 --> 39:45.053
JUST PUT THEM TO BED.

39:47.265 --> 39:48.507
DEREK?

39:48.507 --> 39:51.219
WAIT. JUST...

39:55.143 --> 39:58.186
[ SIGHS ]

39:59.978 --> 40:01.440
DEREK?

40:01.440 --> 40:03.191
JUST WAIT.

40:11.990 --> 40:13.331
I CAN'T DO THIS.
I'M SORRY.

40:13.331 --> 40:14.623
[ STAMMERS ]

40:14.623 --> 40:16.625
TELL ME THAT THIS IS
ALL IN MY HEAD,

40:16.625 --> 40:18.707
THAT THERE ISN'T SOMETHING
BETWEEN US.

40:18.707 --> 40:19.748
I KNOW IT'S THERE.

40:19.748 --> 40:21.920
I LOVE MY WIFE.

40:21.920 --> 40:23.672
I'M MARRIED.

40:23.672 --> 40:27.005
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING OTHER
THAN WHAT I HAVE WITH HER.

40:29.097 --> 40:31.049
I HAVE TO GO.

40:31.049 --> 40:33.722
RIGHT NOW I HAVE TO GO.

40:35.433 --> 40:38.316
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

40:41.480 --> 40:46.444
THAT'S WHY IT'S SO IMPORTANT
FOR US TO REMIND OURSELVES,

40:46.444 --> 40:49.948
FOR US TO REMEMBER.

40:49.948 --> 40:52.280
I AM CALLING POST-IT.

40:52.280 --> 40:54.743
ZOLA AND BAILEY

40:54.743 --> 40:58.376
AND TUMORS ON THE WALLS
AND FERRY BOAT SCRUB CAPS.

41:01.039 --> 41:04.212
I THOUGHT
D.C. WAS EVERYTHING.

41:04.212 --> 41:06.084
AND I WAS WRONG.

41:09.758 --> 41:13.011
YOU...

41:13.011 --> 41:15.804
YOU.

41:15.804 --> 41:18.767
YOU'RE EVERYTHING.

41:18.767 --> 41:20.268
I LOVE YOU,

41:20.268 --> 41:23.101
AND I'M NOT GONNA STOP
LOVING YOU.

41:23.101 --> 41:26.154
MEREDITH,
I CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT YOU.

41:26.154 --> 41:29.658
I DON'T WANT TO LIVE
WITHOUT YOU.

41:29.658 --> 41:34.573
AND I'M GONNA DO EVERYTHING
IN MY POWER TO PROVE IT.

41:44.382 --> 41:46.294
[ SIGHS ]

41:46.294 --> 41:48.126
I CAN LIVE WITHOUT YOU.

41:53.261 --> 41:56.054
BUT I DON'T WANT TO.

41:58.016 --> 42:00.939
I DON'T EVER WANT TO.

42:00.939 --> 42:04.643
JUST BECAUSE WE CAN LIVE
WITHOUT SOMETHING,

42:04.643 --> 42:07.696
IT DOESN'T MEAN WE HAVE TO.
